(Why PostScript, Not PDF) show newline
(-----------------------) show newline
() show newline
(PDF is Adobe's proprietary format dressed in ISO clothing.[^h1]) show newline
(PostScript is:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Open) show newline
(  * Published specification since 1984) show newline
(  * Stable) show newline
(  * Level 3 unchanged since 1997) show newline
(  * Readable) show newline
(  * Plain text you can grep, diff, edit) show newline
(  * Honest) show newline
(  * Describes rendering, doesn't control viewing) show newline
() show newline
(NeXT got it right. The source is the document.[^h2]) show newline
() show newline
([^h1]: Historical: Adobe created PDF in 1993 as a proprietary format,) show newline
(then donated it to ISO in 2008 \(ISO 32000\) after market dominance was) show newline
(achieved. The "open standard" arrived after lock-in.) show newline
() show newline
([^h2]: Historical: NeXT's Display PostScript \(1988\) used PostScript as) show newline
(the native imaging model. What you saw on screen was what the printer) show newline
(rendered. Steve Jobs understood that the document format is the) show newline
(document.) show newline
